Entities - User , file , System (to interact and store files)
3. GET / files?offset=?&limit=. / we can impose of a limit of 10 in backend
on scrolling user shares new offset from UI
1. for security we will have JWT token on header of GET API call
2. API GW will resolve it to user_id and our file system service will
first check if user_id and file_id pair belong to same user for auth
Since files table is simply quering on user_id
we can shard the table by user_id for horzintal
scaling and as there is no join queries can use
dynamo Db no sql . In below table user_id will be parition key
we can use file upload date as sort key althouh not needed
1. So in above design all FRs are done
2. for Non-FRS yes the system is highly available as we have sharded the DB ,
have LB and multiple servers , multi-AZ servers + DB
3. we have authentication at API GW using JWT so system is secure
4. all the operations upload , download are fast as they just interact with DB
and background workers sync the file to S3 . The only speed occured is
of taking the file to S3 , we can reduce latency further by making
whole operation async i.e just push to kafka and executor will take
care of addign entry to DB + adding file to S3
Below are the points to sync the device using websocket connections
1. whenever a device initiates web socket connection , it goes to file system
to request new files whose created_at is greater then latest file
2. whenever a new file is uploaded we basically push to kafka
which is consumed by file system to and sends back to device
3. device can do duplicate resolution on file_id
4. we can use zookeeper for coordination which device has socket connection
websocket connections and file system server mapping
1. So files are bigger we will directly ingest all file to S3
2. So FE will create fingerprint using SHA-256 algo which is used
3. FE will chunk the file lets say in size of 5-10 MB and then make a POST
/upload with metadata details along with fingerprint and chunk details
each chunk also has fingerprint attached and status for each chunk
in payload will be uploading or lets say pending status
4. we get presigned url as response from post request
then client start uploading chunks parallely
4. Once chunk is uploaded through AWS S3 multipart API
to upload chunks parallely , based on suuccess repsonse
FE shows progress and in parally makes API call to update
5. Now what can happen is client can go down before updating BE
in such case when cleint comes back it will rely on BE to get uploaded
chunks , so it could be a possibility a chunk is uploaded again which is fine
as S3 will just override and again notify backned
6. so with above design we can make uploads faster as max network/bw
is getting used , we are direcly making call to S3 which saves network
7. above solution can be used to resume/pause the uploads
